CREATE TABLE interactions (interaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY, lead_id INT, interaction_date TIMESTAMP, interaction_type VARCHAR, outcome VARCHAR);

CREATE TABLE campaigns (campaign_id INT PRIMARY KEY, campaign_name VARCHAR, start_date DATE, end_date DATE, budget DECIMAL);</t><s>SELECT c.customer_name, ca.campaign_name, l.lead_name FROM customers c JOIN leads l ON c.customer_id = l.customer_id JOIN campaigns ca ON l.campaign_id = ca.campaign_id;</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE campaigns (campaign_id INT PRIMARY KEY, campaign_name VARCHAR, start_date DATE, end_date DATE, budget DECIMAL);

CREATE TABLE leads (lead_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_id INT, campaign_id INT, lead_name VARCHAR, lead_email VARCHAR, status VARCHAR);

CREATE TABLE interactions (interaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY, lead_id INT, interaction_date TIMESTAMP, interaction_type VARCHAR, outcome VARCHAR);

CREATE TABLE customers (customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_name VARCHAR, email VARCHAR);</t><s>select c.customer_name, ca.campaign_name, i.interaction_type from customers c join leads l on c.customer_id = l.customer_id join interactions i on l.lead_id = i.lead_id join campaigns ca on l.campaign_id = ca.campaign_id;</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE campaigns (campaign_id INT PRIMARY KEY, campaign_name VARCHAR, start_date DATE, end_date DATE, budget DECIMAL);

CREATE TABLE interactions (interaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY, lead_id INT, interaction_date TIMESTAMP, interaction_type VARCHAR, outcome VARCHAR);

CREATE TABLE customers (customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_name VARCHAR, email VARCHAR);

CREATE TABLE leads (lead_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_id INT, campaign_id INT, lead_name VARCHAR, lead_email VARCHAR, status VARCHAR);</t><s>SELECT c.customer_name, ca.campaign_name, i.interaction_type FROM customers c JOIN leads l ON c.customer_id = l.customer_id JOIN interactions i ON l.lead_id = i.lead_id JOIN campaigns ca ON l.campaign_id = ca.campaign_id;</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE customers (customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_name VARCHAR, email VARCHAR);

CREATE TABLE campaigns (campaign_id INT PRIMARY KEY, campaign_name VARCHAR, start_date DATE, end_date DATE, budget DECIMAL);

CREATE TABLE leads (lead_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_id INT, campaign_id INT, lead_name VARCHAR, lead_email VARCHAR, status VARCHAR);

CREATE TABLE interactions (interaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY, lead_id INT, interaction_date TIMESTAMP, interaction_type VARCHAR, outcome VARCHAR);</t><s>SELECT c.customer_name, l.lead_name, i.interaction_type, i.outcome FROM customers c JOIN leads l ON c.customer_id = l.customer_id JOIN interactions i ON l.lead_id = i.lead_id WHERE i.outcome = 'successful';</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE customers (customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_name VARCHAR, email VARCHAR);

CREATE TABLE interactions (interaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY, lead_id INT, interaction_date TIMESTAMP, interaction_type VARCHAR, outcome VARCHAR);

CREATE TABLE leads (lead_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_id INT, campaign_id INT, lead_name VARCHAR, lead_email VARCHAR, status VARCHAR);

CREATE TABLE campaigns (campaign_id INT PRIMARY KEY, campaign_name VARCHAR, start_date DATE, end_date DATE, budget DECIMAL);</t><s>SELECT c.customer_name, l.lead_name, i.interaction_type, i.outcome FROM customers c JOIN leads l ON c.customer_id = l.customer_id JOIN interactions i ON l.lead_id = i.lead_id WHERE i.outcome = 'successful';</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE customers (customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_name VARCHAR, email VARCHAR);

CREATE TABLE responses (response_id INT PRIMARY KEY, email_id INT, lead_id INT, response_type VARCHAR(20), response_date DATETIME)

CREATE TABLE leads (lead_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_id INT, campaign_id INT, status VARCHAR(20), source VARCHAR(50))</t><s>select customer_id,name,email from customers where customer_id = 1;</s>

CREATE TABLE responses (response_id INT PRIMARY KEY, email_id INT, lead_id INT, response_type VARCHAR(20), response_date DATETIME)

CREATE TABLE customers (customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), email VARCHAR(50), phone VARCHAR(15))

CREATE TABLE campaigns (campaign_id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), start_date DATE, end_date DATE, budget DECIMAL(10,2))</t><s>select customer_id,name,email from customers where customer_id = 1;</s>

CREATE TABLE responses (response_id INT PRIMARY KEY, email_id INT, lead_id INT, response_type VARCHAR(20), response_date DATETIME)</t><s>select campaign_id,name,budget from campaigns where campaign_id = 1;</s>

CREATE TABLE responses (response_id INT PRIMARY KEY, email_id INT, lead_id INT, response_type VARCHAR(20), response_date DATETIME)</t><s>SELECT email_id,lead_id,subject FROM emails WHERE email_id = 1;</s>

CREATE TABLE responses (response_id INT PRIMARY KEY, email_id INT, lead_id INT, response_type VARCHAR(20), response_date DATETIME)

CREATE TABLE campaigns (campaign_id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), start_date DATE, end_date DATE, budget DECIMAL(10,2))

CREATE TABLE emails (email_id INT PRIMARY KEY, lead_id INT, subject VARCHAR(100), body TEXT, sent_date DATETIME)</t><s>select * from customers,leads where customers.customer_id = leads.customer_id;</s>

CREATE TABLE emails (email_id INT PRIMARY KEY, lead_id INT, subject VARCHAR(100), body TEXT, sent_date DATETIME)

CREATE TABLE campaigns (campaign_id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), start_date DATE, end_date DATE, budget DECIMAL(10,2))

CREATE TABLE responses (response_id INT PRIMARY KEY, email_id INT, lead_id INT, response_type VARCHAR(20), response_date DATETIME)</t><s>select * from customers,leads where customers.customer_id = leads.customer_id;</s>

CREATE TABLE responses (response_id INT PRIMARY KEY, email_id INT, lead_id INT, response_type VARCHAR(20), response_date DATETIME)

CREATE TABLE emails (email_id INT PRIMARY KEY, lead_id INT, subject VARCHAR(100), body TEXT, sent_date DATETIME)</t><s>select * from campaigns,leads where campaigns.campaign_id = leads.campaign_id;</s>

CREATE TABLE leads (lead_id INT PRIMARY KEY, customer_id INT, campaign_id INT, status VARCHAR(20), source VARCHAR(50))</t><s>select * from campaigns,leads where campaigns.campaign_id = leads.campaign_id;</s>

CREATE TABLE responses (response_id INT PRIMARY KEY, email_id INT, lead_id INT, response_type VARCHAR(20), response_date DATETIME)

CREATE TABLE campaigns (campaign_id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), start_date DATE, end_date DATE, budget DECIMAL(10,2))

CREATE TABLE emails (email_id INT PRIMARY KEY, lead_id INT, subject VARCHAR(100), body TEXT, sent_date DATETIME)</t><s>select * from emails,responses where emails.email_id = responses.email_id;</s>

CREATE TABLE customers (customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), email VARCHAR(50), phone VARCHAR(15))

CREATE TABLE emails (email_id INT PRIMARY KEY, lead_id INT, subject VARCHAR(100), body TEXT, sent_date DATETIME)

CREATE TABLE responses (response_id INT PRIMARY KEY, email_id INT, lead_id INT, response_type VARCHAR(20), response_date DATETIME)</t><s>select * from emails,responses where emails.email_id = responses.email_id;</s>

CREATE TABLE emails (email_id INT PRIMARY KEY, lead_id INT, subject VARCHAR(100), body TEXT, sent_date DATETIME)

CREATE TABLE campaigns (campaign_id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), start_date DATE, end_date DATE, budget DECIMAL(10,2))

CREATE TABLE responses (response_id INT PRIMARY KEY, email_id INT, lead_id INT, response_type VARCHAR(20), response_date DATETIME)</t><s>select * from emails,responses where emails.email_id = responses.email_id;</s>

CREATE TABLE campaigns (campaign_id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), start_date DATE, end_date DATE, budget DECIMAL(10,2))

CREATE TABLE customers (customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), email VARCHAR(50), phone VARCHAR(15))

CREATE TABLE emails (email_id INT PRIMARY KEY, lead_id INT, subject VARCHAR(100), body TEXT, sent_date DATETIME)</t><s>select * from emails,responses where emails.email_id = responses.email_id;</s>
